Camoufox: spoof system-ui generic font family to match navigator.platform.

Upstream Firefox's gfxPlatformFontList::GetSystemUIFontFamilies() resolves
the `system-ui` generic via LookAndFeel::GetFont(StyleSystemFont::Menu, ...).
On Linux that returns the real GTK system font (e.g. "Cantarell", "Ubuntu",
"Noto Sans") regardless of how navigator.platform / userAgent is spoofed.

CreepJS picks this up under `headless.systemFonts` -> system-ui resolves
to a Linux font even when we claim to be macOS / Windows. This patch
intercepts before LookAndFeel::GetFont() and returns:

  - "Helvetica"     when navigator.platform starts with "Mac"
  - "Segoe UI"      when navigator.platform starts with "Win"
  - (falls through) otherwise

navigator.platform is plumbed through the existing camoucfg /
MaskConfig::GetString("navigator.platform") channel that the rest of
Camoufox's spoofing already uses. MaskConfig.hpp is already included
into gfxPlatformFontList.cpp by font-hijacker.patch (which sorts before
this patch alphabetically), and gfx/thebes/moz.build already has
LOCAL_INCLUDES += ["/camoucfg"], so we only need to insert the spoof
check.

Bug: daijro/camoufox#598

--- a/gfx/thebes/gfxPlatformFontList.cpp
+++ b/gfx/thebes/gfxPlatformFontList.cpp
@@ -2115,6 +2115,32 @@
   nsFont systemFont;
   gfxFontStyle fontStyle;
   nsAutoString systemFontName;
+
+  // Camoufox: spoof system-ui based on navigator.platform so we don't leak
+  // the real OS's GTK/Win/Mac system font through CSS `font: system-ui`
+  // resolution. See daijro/camoufox#598.
+  if (auto platform = MaskConfig::GetString("navigator.platform")) {
+    const std::string& p = platform.value();
+    auto starts_with = [&](const char* prefix) {
+      size_t n = std::strlen(prefix);
+      return p.size() >= n &&
+             std::equal(prefix, prefix + n, p.begin(),
+                        [](char a, char b) {
+                          return std::tolower(static_cast<unsigned char>(a)) ==
+                                 std::tolower(static_cast<unsigned char>(b));
+                        });
+    };
+    if (starts_with("mac")) {
+      *aFamilies.AppendElement() = "Helvetica"_ns;
+      return;
+    }
+    if (starts_with("win")) {
+      *aFamilies.AppendElement() = "Segoe UI"_ns;
+      return;
+    }
+    // Linux / iPhone / unknown: fall through to upstream behavior.
+  }
+
   if (aFontVisibilityProvider
           ? aFontVisibilityProvider->ShouldResistFingerprinting(
                 RFPTarget::FontVisibilityRestrictGenerics)
